The paper discusses a caching architecture for storage subsystems in computer systems, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The use of Solid-State Drives (SSDs) and their performance characteristics make this paper relevant to the sub-categories of Architecture (cs.AR), Databases (cs.DB), Operating Systems (cs.OS), and Systems and Control (cs.SY).
